From: Igor Kanyuka <ifelmail@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 11 Mar 2025 12:10:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 203/205] Add required MemberId to the EventRecord definition

The EventRecord definition requires MemberId [1]. It's suggested to be
a 0 based index [2] for Redfish 1.6 and above. The Event v1_4_0 we use
is part of the 2019.1 release [3]. While Redfish 1.6 is dated by
2018-08-23 [4]. So, add the required property and fill it out in a way
the standard suggests.

It's not being populated in the formatEventLogEntry, as it's possible,
that the built event will be filtered, so the MemberId will be a zero
based index in the array before filtering.

[1] MemberId is a required property for EventRecord
```
$ curl -s https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/Event.v1_4_0.json | jq .definitions.EventRecord.required
[
  "EventType",
  "MessageId",
  "MemberId"
]
```
[2] MemberId description:
```
 curl -s https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/Event.v1_4_0.json | jq .definitions.EventRecord.properties.MemberId
{
  "description": "This is the identifier for the member within the collection.",
  "longDescription": "The value of this string shall uniquely identify the member within the collection.  For services supporting Redfish v1.6 or higher, this value shall be the zero-based array index.",
  "readonly": true,
  "type": "string"
}
```
[3] Release
```
 curl -s https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/Event.v1_4_0.json | jq .release
"2019.1"
```
[4] https://www.dmtf.org/sites/default/files/standards/documents/DSP0266_1.6.0.pdf

Signed-off-by: Igor Kanyuka <ifelmail@gmail.com>
Change-Id: I99fcdcdccc97bfa39581d3e42ef407a8cfadaa83
---
 redfish-core/src/subscription.cpp | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/redfish-core/src/subscription.cpp b/redfish-core/src/subscription.cpp
index f81fdc6..7f61b9b 100644
--- a/redfish-core/src/subscription.cpp
+++ b/redfish-core/src/subscription.cpp
@@ -212,6 +212,7 @@ void Subscription::filterAndSendEventLogs(
             logEntry.messageArgs.begin(), logEntry.messageArgs.end());
 
         nlohmann::json::object_t bmcLogEntry;
+        uint64_t memberId = 0;
         if (event_log::formatEventLogEntry(
                 eventId, logEntry.id, logEntry.messageId, messageArgsView,
                 logEntry.timestamp, userSub->customText, bmcLogEntry) != 0)
@@ -236,6 +237,7 @@ void Subscription::filterAndSendEventLogs(
             }
         }
 
+        bmcLogEntry["MemberId"] = std::to_string(memberId++);
         logEntryArray.emplace_back(std::move(bmcLogEntry));
         eventId++;
     }
